the prolonged maritime\nstrike n 1948.\nTHE CLEANERS\nOF\nWRANGELL\nDrv Cleaning Pressing\nAlterations\nProprieto-s\nMU. MRS. J. R. NEWKIRK\nJOHNSON MACHINE\nWORKS\n\nGUS JOHNSON\nProprietor\n\nGENERAL BOAT REPAIR\nWINTER PROGRAM\nRED MEN LODGE\nDANCES POT LUCK LUNCH\ni\u2019ed Men Hall\nFebruary 12\nFebruary 26\nMarch 12\nMarch 26\nApril 9\n(Admission By Card Only)\n\nDR. E. J. WHEELER j!\n\nI DENTI8T\n\nOffice Located In\n\nWheeler Building\n\nPhone 64\n1\ni\"j. i 1 1 t \u00bb'i' 'H- \u25a0>'i1'!'\u00bb*\nTANNING I\nj SEND US ALL YOUR FURS AND SKINS TO BE TANNED\nQuick, Efficient, Reliable Workmanship\nYour Work will Be Returned IMMEDIATELY After\nIt Is Finished 1!\nVALCAUDA FUR CO.\nNational Building Seattle, Wash.\n..i-jBfflByyrrKryyrowT\u2022;yyr^jcv\u00bbfr-,~'~. \"X'SPf: \u2022r\nSheppard Six-Cylinder Ma\nrine Engines (12C, 12F). 56-62\nHP. Completely equipped,\nready to go. Other Marine\nPropulsion Engines from 3.5\nto 100 H.P., and Auxiliaries\nwith bilge and fire pump, air\ncompressor, generator.\nT TERR\u2019S safe, dependable, eco\nnomical Diesel power for\nSMALL marine engine users! Shep\npard Marine Diesels do any job\nyour present engine will do\u2014at one\nquarter the fuel cost\u2014with reduced\nfire hazards, less maintenance, fewer\nbreakdowns! Pushbutton or auto\nmatic starting. Injector has only\none moving part. Delivered com\nplete, ready to operate, no extras to\nbuy. Find out how a Sheppard\nDiesel can help you. Phone or write\ntoday for FREE Sheppard material\ngiving facts, figures, specifications!\nPatfs Radio Electric\n0\nWrangell had 78 northbound\nships carrying mail in 1948 and\n63 southbound ships. Of these, 44\nnorthbound and 44 southbound\nwere C.P.R. vessels.\nCancellations out of Wrangell\u2019s\npost office during 1948 totaled\n214,184 or an increase of some\n8,000 over 1947.\n26 ALASKA TOWNS\nRECEIVE $2,752,856.49\nJUNEAU Twenty-six munici\npalities received a total if $2,752,\n856.49 in refunds from the Terri\ntory during the biennium wMch\nstarted on January 1, 1947, and\nended on December 31, 1948, a re\nport of Territorial Auditor Frank\nA. Boyle discloses.\nOf this total, $442,379.71 had\nnot yet been* paid on December 31\nbecause of the shortage of funds.\nMost of the total was in refunds\nto schools and tuition. Direct re\nfunds to schools amounted to $2,\n311,682.65; tuition for students\nliving outside of municipalities but\nattending city schools came to\n$63,478; refunds on liquor licenses\ntotaled $356,933.34 and refunds on\nthe tax on coin operated machines\ncame to $22,762.50.\nAnchorage received the greatest\namount of Territorial refunds,\n$664,867.27, including $550,689.76\nin school add; $16,152.50 in tui\ntion; $91,725.01 in liquor license\nrefunds and $6,300 in slot mach\nine license refunds.\nSecond on the list was Ketchi\nkan with a total of $325,756.5.6 In\naid. including $279,591.81 for\nschools; $5,546 for tuition; $36,\n551 for liquor licenses and $4,-'\n088.75 for slot machines.\nNext in line came Fairbanks\nand Juneau. Wrangell, in ninth\nplace, with SJtka, Kodiak, Peters\nburg and Nome ahead, received\n$94,120.06.\n1 I I 1 I M\nPUBLIC HEALTH NOTES\nBy Arne Bulkeley\nPublic Health Nurse\nThe Well Baby Conference will\nbe held Friday. February IS, from\n9 to XI a. m., in the Health Cen\nter, Room 201, Federal Building\nDr. John O. Bangeman, Health Of\nficer, will be present to examine\nand immunize the children against\nsmallpox, diphtheria, and whoop\ning cough. The Well Child Confer\nence is not established alone for\nthe purpose of immunization al\nthough this is a large part of its\nwork. The main purpose is that it\nis established as a place where ed\nucation of the parent is done by\nthe physician rather than by the\nlay-magazine or poorly informed\nrelatives and neighbors. It offers\nan opportunity to appraise the in\ndividual child and to determine\ndeviations from normal growth and\nbehavior and to make plans for\ntheir correction.\nIt is recommended that a child\nin his first year of life see the\nphysician once a month; in the\nsecond year, every three months,\nand from two to six years of age\nevery six months. It is the par\nents\u2019 responsibility to see that this\nis done. The Well Child Confer\nence is a community service and\nas community members everyone\ncan make use of it.\nFebruary 1J, was National Social\nHygiene Day, a day in which to\nstop to consider the progress made\nin the fight against syphilis and\ngonorrhea. The sooial hygiene facts\nare good, showing some progress,\nbut the diseases are still un\nconquered. It is estimated that a\nbout three million people in the\nSERVICE\n^BARGAINS\n1 7-FT. BEFBIGEBATOB EXCELLENT CONDITION\n$100.00\n1 SPEED QUEEN WASHING MACHINE LIKE NEW\n$95.00\nin Pan American\u2019s 16 years\nof Alaskan service\nN A small package or heavy\nmachinery, you save by Clipper\nCargo. Big savings on shipments\nover 100 lbs. on some commodi\nties, too. Only light packing neces\nsary saves shipping weight and\npacking costs. 'Ybu also save on in\nsurance rates, inventory and ware\nhousing costs.\nClipper Cargo gives you quicker\ndelivery helps you open new\nmarkets for perishables, get quicker\npayment. Offers convenient C.O.D.\nand collect service to many countries.\nLearn all the advantages of Clipper\nCargo. Let this fast service make\nmoney for you. Just call\nART NELSON, Agent\nMoney-saving\nrates between\nKETCHIKAN\nAND\nSEATTLE\n12* per lb.\non shipments of\n100 lb. or more\n\n8* per lb. on\nshipments of fish from\nKetchikan to Seattle\n(Min. wt. 100 lbs.)\ne\nSpecial low rates\non furs and hides\n11 lbs. or more\ne\nBIG SAVINGS\nTO POINTS\nIN ALASKA, TOO\nPaiv Amfrlcas\nWorld Airways\ncitpptr .TrfJe Ma*k Pa 9 Am ft it J9 i !UU)i.l .1\nWrangell Electric Supply\nCOMPLETE NEW LINE OF\nRADIO BATTERIES\nNEW RADIOS\nBattery Electric\nPHILCO R. C. A.\nUnited States have syphilis and a\nbout fifteen million have gonor\nrhea. It is impossible to be blind\nto this staggering number of peo\nple for what you don't know can\nhurt you. Information on these\ndiseases is the basis for fighting\nthem and it is essential that every\ncitizen become informed about\nthem.\n\nCOMMUNICATION\n+4\nTo the People of Wrangell:\nAlthough the fair name o f\nWrangell is ably represented in\nJuneau at the present political\npow wow, now in session, by our\nswn Mrs. Doris Barnes and Jim\nNolan, and granted that we do\nreceive the recognition that we\nare rightfully entitled to there is\ni group of young men who are\nilso carrying the name of our city\nto every nook and cranny of the\nrerritory. We refer, of course, to\nthe Wrang'ell towui basketball\nteam.\nOperating now, and for some\ntime past, as a non-profit organiz\nition and at present without bene\nfit of a competent coach, these\ntoys have established a record,\nlecond to none, in games won and\nclean sportsmanship that will be\ndifficult to equal.\nTraveling under difficulties, in\nsmall boats, these \"Ambassadors\nof good will\" arrive, sans cheering\nsection, in the surrounding towns,\nmany times but a few hours be\nfore the game time. Tired and\nweary though they may be, they\nhave consistently gained the\npraises of civic leaders for their\ndisplay of fine fellowship and\nplaying ability in every town\nplayed this season.\nThe Alaska Native Brotherhood\nof Wrangell, realizing the import\nance of maintaining a recreational\nprogram for our young people af\nter they graduate from high\nschool, are happy to announce that\nour town team will no longer op\nerate under the difficulties of the\npast.\nSaturday night. February 12,\nwill see the first in a series of\nbenefit Bingos sponsored by the\nAlaska Native Sisterhood and\nBrotherhood to obtain funds for\nthe assistance of a long neglected\ngroup of fine ycung athletes. The\npublic is cordially invited to at\ntend and show these boys that we\ndo appreciate that they have,\nthrough their efforts, put Wran\ngell \"on the map\u201d of athletic ac\ntivity in Southeastern Alaska.\nALASKA NATIVE\nBROTHERHOOD\nEllis Air\nLines\nKetchikan\u2014Wrangell \u2014Petersburg\u2014.1 unenu\nTRIPS TO SITX EVERY TUUTtsDAY\nFor Tlfke'n nm1 R\u00ab-,erv\u00bbil\nSEE ART NELSON PHONE: 6\naaaMMMMMHMMHMMBHBaHMMaaHHHMIMliMIlaHBMMaaMaMiaiaiMnJ\n5 A VE TIME\nSA VE THE PIECES\nOf your broken lenses and airmail your\nbroken glasses to\nDrs. C. PI. R. L. Carlson\nBOX 468 KETCHIKAN, ALASKA\nWe give yon quick airmail replacement\nservice in our complete optical laboratory\nEYES EXAMINED GLASSES FITTED\nOWL GAPE\nREGULAR MEALS SNACKS\nPhone Red 77\nWEEK DAYS SATURDAYS HOLIDAYS\n10:00 A. M. to 1:00 A. M. 10:00 A. M. to 2 A. M.\nSHIRLEY HARTLEY, Proprietor\nINSURANCE\nIt\nFIRE MARINE LIABILITY\nCAMPBELL BROTHERS jj\nPhone 22\nRitchie Traos. Co.\nTRAVEL UP THE SCEHIC 8TIEIHE RIVER\nOpen May 6 to October 1ft\nTELEGRAPH CHEEK, 1. C BIO GAME KUHTDIO\nud Kama dutebict","height":"25700","width":"19152"}}
